-- Tobacco From Malawi Sold For 34% Below Government-Mandated Price Last Week
-- B y   F r a n k   J o m o
-- 2010-11-08T06:32:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-08/tobacco-from-malawi-sold-for-34-below-government-mandated-price-last-week.html
The average price of tobacco in
Malawi, the world’s largest producer of burley tobacco, traded
34 percent below the government’s price of $2 per kilogram.  The leaf sold for an average $1.32 per kilogram (2.2
pounds) in the week through Nov. 5, compared with $1.33 a week
earlier, Auction Holdings Ltd., which manages the country’s
auction floors, said in an advertisement published in the Daily
Times newspaper today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Frank Jomo in Blantyre at 
 fjomo@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alastair Reed at 
 areed12@bloomberg.net  